> Curious if this applies to libc++ as well as libstdc++

@sdaftuar and I have tried reading through the [libc++ implementation of hash tables](https://github.com/llvm-mirror/libcxx/blob/master/include/__hash_table) to find the equivalent caching clause to [what's in libstdc++](https://github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc/blob/41d6b10e96a1de98e90a7c0378437c3255814b16/libstdc%2B%2B-v3/include/bits/hashtable.h#L44-L49), but so far we haven't been able to find it. Does anyone know where this happens in libc++ (clang)?

I'll report back soon with clang-based benches.
